<br>
<br>
     &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I've been reading the Boards trying to figure out what may help our class out. I believe Nanaeve comes the closest to what I beleive.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp First let me say that when I hear a Wizard shout &quot;Looking for a group&quot; I don't even want to group with him. I'm sorry to say I feel this way and I'm a Wizard myself. It's a shame I feel this way and is just plain not fair. I would group with any other class first. This is terrible.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp When I'm in a group sitting and medding every other fight, I feel guilty taking experience. I'm sure the other members of the group feel the same way. I'm constantly mana managing and deciding if and when I should cast. I know the other group members see this and become to resent watching me medding while they are fighting. &quot;Master of D&amp;D&quot; that seems funny at times when I'm low on mana, which is always in a group. I have been tempted many times to cast my level one spell  &quot;They think I am helping&quot; SO THEY KEEP ME IN THE GROUP, BECAUSE THEY WONT KNOW IF I HIT FOR 10 DAMAGE OR 500 DAMAGE ANYWAYS. At least it looks better than sitting there medding.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The solution I feel the most comfortable with, which has been suggested by others, is to give Wizards a mana regeneration bonus when grouped, per members in the group. It has been suggested anywhere's from 10% to 20% per person in the group for mana regeneration.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp This would accomplish 2 things, #1 Would help with the fear VI has of a Wizard becoming a solo machine if they make spells more powerful. #2 It would make a Wizard in a group able to cast more than Once or twice in a fight and maybe actually do an even amount of damage to a mob as others in the group. I for one would become a searcher for groups, just for the extra mana regeneration. Wouldn't it be nice to see a Wizard actually casting in a group instead of holding back . The group would appreciate the extra casts also and maybe bring into line the &quot;Master of D&amp;D&quot; so that a group may actually believe that a Wizard may come close to that truth.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uupyer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Upyer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 1:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Balance</span><hr size=1> A grouped mana regen is not the answer. It basically involves us accepting we are a flawed class and lets Verant off the hook from fixing us. Mana regen yes - but if it's just group only to make us more attractive it's a bit like putting rouge on a tart.<br>
<br>
We are offensive casteres - fix our offensive capability and let us do more damage. Faster mana regen yes - but not on someone elses terms because we feel guilty about being equal.<br>
<br>
It saddens me to see how far we have fallen.<br>
 <p>Uproar Solarwind 51 Wizard<br>
Founder Guild Quintessence
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxyntic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xyntic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 2:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Balance</span><hr size=1> The issue that Verant is stuck on involves soloing.  They do not really want to increase our ability to solo..and I tend to agree.  What they have failed to notice is what makes soloing (i.e. kiting) work:  The ability to snare a mob, run away, then begin casting and have the spell land BEFORE the mob is within melee range, then running away again to repeat the process.<br>
It's a rather simple equation once you look at the variables involved.<br>
A.  Melee range of Mob_01.<br>
B.  Snared running speed of Mob_01.<br>
C.  Cast time of the Wizards' spell.<br>
D.  Range of the spell.<br>
<br>
A_Mob_01 is at coordinate 0,0,0 with a melee range of 25.<br>
A_Mob_01 can run at snared speed of 100 in 5 seconds.<br>
Kiting_Spell_01 casts in 5 seconds.<br>
Kiting_spell_01 has a range of 200.<br>
<br>
This means that I can stand at coordinate 200,0,0 and snare A_Mob_01.  It will take A_Mob_01 8.75 seconds to reach melee range.  Immediately after snaring, A_Wizard_01 casts Kiting_Spell_01 which takes 5 seconds.  When the spell hits, A_Mob_01 is now 3.75 seconds away from melee range.  A_Wizard_01 now has 3.75 seconds to move out of melee range.<br>
<br>
<br>
Verant can triple our damage output, increase our mana regen by an insane amount, cut our resists to zero and not unbalance us by simply changing the cast times so that the casting time is greater than the time required for a given mob to travel the distance between the casting range and melee range OR change the casting distance so that the current recast time is still means the mob gets within melee range just as the spell lands.<br>
<br>
I don't know about you, but knowing that every time I cast a spell while kiting a snared mob means it gets at least 1 attempt to pound my little brains in would deter me from soloing..but it would not affect hinder my performance in a group.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.elddarcaste.com/"target="web"><img src="http://www.elddarcaste.com/sigfile1.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 3:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Group vs. solo.</span><hr size=1> You're absolutely correct about &quot;solo&quot; deterents.  But I also agree with the group specific additions to our class.  Right now, it isn't even a question of whether we solo well or not.  I DON'T WANT to solo anymore.  Been doing it forever and it has worn thin.  However, if verant were to nerf it, they would nerf away the only thing that we have been consistantly able to do to get ourselves consistant exp.<br>
<br>
I still believe the issue goes along the line of group effectivness.  I can honestly say that increasing our mana regen or damage output would NOT increase my desire to solo.  I hate it, its antisocial, and this is a community oriented game.  (so they say.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  But it WOULD make it so I can actually PARTICIPATE in the group setting rather than sit 75% of the time... AT LEAST!  I think the group based mana regen idea is actually quite good.  Is it the only possibility?  No way.  But it makes us a touch more effective in the setting.  That way, we can actually pull our weight, but it does nothing to enhance soloing.  Yes, there are more things that are needed.  There is no SINGLE fix that will correct our numerous problems.  This idea really only applies to the standard exp group.  Not epic raids, uber gods, etc.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorionsun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>orionsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 5:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group vs. solo.</span><hr size=1> You know when I was a young wiz I never soloed. As far as I knew, no wiz was soloing then heh. Nowadays you see lots of wiz soloing. It just shows how the wiz class in general is viewed by the populace. <br>
<br>
A typical group needs 1-3 tanks, 1-3 casters, ench/bard, cleric, but only needs 1 evacer which there are lots of druids so wiz get left out alot of times. <br>
<br>
One of these times, Im going to group all the wiz lfg at the zone and head to charasis heh. 4 wiz aeing will drop mobs pretty fast heh. <br>
<br>
Orionsun <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=quiksilver1>Quiksilver1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 5:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Casting Time</span><hr size=1> My only problem with increasing casting time is that we are the masters of fast damage.  Rather I would prefer they took AWAY the snare line (Bonds of Force and Atol's) both invaluable to kiting, and just left us with root.  In soloing without snare, root poses a very decent threat, if it breaks, you only get one shot to recast it (maybe) and if it doesn't stick you get hammered on.  Remember the root and nuke tactics before you hit 29 or had Jboots? Well anyway if they increased us in other ways so we could assist the group with more mana, faster regen and better damage, they could gladly take my soloabiity away, but in return they'd have to make sure that I was desperately needed by a group like a cleric or warrior.  They have to make up their minds, either make us gods at soloing or make us valuable to a group, I'm sick of being stuck in between.  I just want to be good at something other than &quot;breaking mez with AoE spells&quot; (another line of spells helpful in quad kiting/soloing but very few groups know the value of or the place for it).  Make me valuable to an xp group please (=<br>
<br>
Yaldin<br>
47 Wizard<br>
Karana Server<br>
Storm`s Justice<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulimdul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LimDul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 5:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group vs. solo.</span><hr size=1> Just for clarity sake...are we sure that's the reason why VI doesn't give us more damage output?  I agree it has nothing to do with solo vrs grouping.<br>
<br>
I've been forming my own assumptions that they just don't want to speed up the game any.<br>
<br>
So if that's the case, there is a major difference in opinion...our arguement is that giving us more damage potential will actually INCREASE our group-ability.  VI is thinking quite the opposite.<br>
<br>
Hmmmm....just thinking out loud.<br>
-- Lim'Dul <p><HR>
