</TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uazlinon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azlinon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/16/01 9:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group vs. solo.</span><hr size=1> I personally don't think that verant should change our damage on spells at all (with a few sspecific level as exceptions).  The problem lies in our efficiency, not in mana regen, etc.  The same regen rate is 2 times as effective if your spells cost half the mana.  What they need to do is shorten SOME cast times, and then mana requirements across the board.  This should be something like half the mana required (ie IC should take 200m, not 400).  I feel we should significantly outdamage any melee but a rogue, and even then only fall a bit short, maybe 10 percent?  Give any of the mobs that you would be in fear of us multi-kiting slightly faster run speeds to compensate (also helps the true problem with quad-kiting druids) for the aditional damage we can do on a bar of mana.  There is NO excuse for any class doing more damage than us over  (with the exception of a rogue long-term).  We should not however outdamage a rogue, as we have the ability to pick more precisely when to apply the damage.  Upping mana regen would result in less time on our butts between fights.  Upping efficiency would result in the same time for a full med, but the ability to do twice that damage.  I would much rather be up and participating in a group the entire fight and then med than to fight 1min, sit on my butt for 5, and then add a couple nukes again. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=6029">Azlinon Seflarian</a> of <a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/divinesymphony">Divine Symphony</a><br>
Guild-Leader<br>
Wizard of Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearedanymore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfeared anymore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/16/01 10:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group vs. solo.</span><hr size=1> CAREFUL !!! Do NOT suggest nerfs until they fix the damage/regen isues or you'll be seeing increased casting times..and no fixes.  FIX first, and THEN nerf solo ability IF needed.  Antecedent, consequential relationship on these patches.  No more nerfs..kiting is only desirable part of wizard right now.  Why nerf it anyway ? It is very difficult and dangerous to master..alot of things can and will go wrong.  AE's use would be what then ?  I live on a PvP server, so AE's in combat with group do not work, and even if I couldn't use AE's in group battle's..you want cast time increasesd ?  Hmm seems that would adversely affect the damage/time ratio even further..A familiar with scaling abilities with levels seems very cool, or just better mana efficiency would work well as well..casting times..leave them alone.  Anyway, what is wrong with the Wizard soloing some of the time ?  Wizards of lore were ussually reclusive.  I understand your attempt here, but Verant needs to get over this supposed unbalanced soloing issue.  This is what is KILLING Verants incentive to fix this class.  Try soloing Wizards from 1-29 (level you get BoF), before you can effectively Quad kite (even twinked, is very difficult) ?  Now, try soloing a Warrior (esp a twinked one) to 29..compare time played..OK, so we never get to solo better than a warior if you nerf quading and that is fair ? This is not a Flame, but Verant needs some positive direction..let's not even suggest more nerfs please, even if it may &quot;allow&quot; verant to make positive fixes. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearedanymore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfeared anymore</A> at: 3/16/01 3:27:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ublastum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blastum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/01 2:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> why not make us better at soloing?</span><hr size=1>   Why all the fear that a wizard with more mana could solo, say, two mobs in a row.   Does that ability make a necro a god?  Not really.  <br>
  I just don't understand the apprehension there.  What great harm would be done if I could solo two mobs in a row , and then med?  Would I reach level 60 in a week or something? LOL<br>
  Even if I could quad kite two pulls in a row, I see balance there also, with the risks involved.<br>
<br>
Blastum 59 Wizard of Brell<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uakailen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akailen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/22/01 8:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What about experience adjusting?</span><hr size=1> Okay, this is a long shot and I have no idea on how difficult it would be to implement, but why not make experience aquired when soloing less effective for leveling than experience aquired in a group?  That way Verant could do the fixes and not worry about soloing, because no one is going to want to spend 6 hours worth of soloing time for experience that could be obtained in 1 or 2 hours with a group.  This would hurt Necromancers I guess since they are supposed to be good at soloing so I don't know, just my ramblings.<br>
<br>
Akailen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyofallien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yofallien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/23/01 2:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about experience adjusting?</span><hr size=1> VI tried &quot;experience adjusting&quot;  They implemented the bonus for full groups.  That's great for full groups.  But it doesn't do anything to help me get into a group.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I'd love to see faster mana regen/more damage/ yadda yadda.  The funny thing, even with a faster mana regen you won't be able to contribute that much more to the group.  Doubt me? ask any wiz that overburns on a regular basis.  Without a couple of tanks taunting or another wiz to play ping pong with (we know how the tanks love that routine) you are going to be a doing a lot of <br>
